INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'e3a5478a-f6c1-4e65-8bca-61b37a1cdb98',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$anthropic_api + LlamaIndex — Wiring Claude into Document Indexing and Query Engines$escape$,
  $escape$LlamaIndex's `Anthropic` LLM adapter routes synthesis through Claude, replacing the default OpenAI calls. Wire it in globally via `Settings.llm` and every downstream component — query engines, chat engines, sub-question decomposers — inherits it automatically.

For document loading, `SimpleDirectoryReader` handles local files; swap to LlamaHub loaders for Notion, S3, or PostgreSQL sources. `VectorStoreIndex.from_documents()` chunks docs using `Settings.chunk_size` (default 1024 tokens), embeds them, and builds a retrievable in-memory index. Persist to `pgvector` via `PGVectorStore` for production durability.

At query time, `as_query_engine()` controls two critical levers: `similarity_top_k` (chunks retrieved) and `response_mode` (how Claude synthesizes them). `compact` concatenates all chunks into one Claude call — cheapest. `tree_summarize` fans out multiple Claude calls and recursively merges — best for large corpora. `refine` updates a running answer over each chunk sequentially — highest fidelity, most tokens.

Claude's 200k context window means you can push `similarity_top_k` to 20+ before hitting limits — unlike shorter-context models, `tree_summarize` is rarely needed. Default to `compact` and tune `chunk_overlap` (default 200 tokens) to preserve cross-chunk context.$escape$,
  $escape$from llama_index.core import VectorStoreIndex, SimpleDirectoryReader, Settings
from llama_index.llms.anthropic import Anthropic

Settings.llm = Anthropic(
    model="claude-opus-4-6",
    api_key="sk-ant-..."
)
Settings.chunk_size = 512
Settings.chunk_overlap = 64

docs = SimpleDirectoryReader("./data").load_data()
index = VectorStoreIndex.from_documents(docs)

query_engine = index.as_query_engine(
    similarity_top_k=10,
    response_mode="compact"
)
print(query_engine.query("What are the key architectural decisions?"))$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
